item.title: Qld parents slain, son arrested in NSW
item.description: A man accused of murdering his parents in Brisbane has been caught more than 900 kilometres away on a Sydney highway.

item.title: UK daily virus death toll increases by 170
item.description: The number of people who have died in the United Kingdom after testing positive for COVID-19 has risen by 170 to 34,636, business minister Alok Sharma says, the lowest increase in the official death toll since March 24.

item.title: NDIS a bad experience for workers: survey
item.description: Four out of five disability workers say the National Disability Insurance Scheme has been a negative experience for them, a survey reveals.

item.title: French virus death toll rises to 28,108
item.description: France has reported 483 new coronavirus deaths, bringing the total to 28,108 as the country eases out of a two-month lockdown.

item.title: ‘No spike’ in cases in US areas reopening
item.description: There has so far not been a surge in coronavirus cases in areas of the United States that are reopening, US Health Secretary Alex Azar says.

item.title: Italy death toll lowest since March 9
item.description: The daily death toll from the COVID-19 epidemic in Italy has fallen to 145 - the lowest since March 9 - against 153 the day before, the Civil Protection Agency says.

item.title: Israeli govt start ends 17-month deadlock
item.description: After three inconclusive elections since late 2018 - and multiple last-minute delays - Israel's long-awaited new government has finally been sworn in, with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu vowing the time had come to annex West Bank settlements pending US approval.

item.title: Fatality reported in Canadian jet crash
item.description: A jet from the Canadian air force's Snowbirds team that was on a national tour to lift spirits during the coronavirus outbreak has crashed into a neighbourhood in Kamloops, British Columbia, with reports one crew member has died.

item.title: Australia’s virus death toll rises to 99
item.description: Australia's coronavirus death toll has edged closer to 100 after a man died in NSW, while Victoria moves to clamp down on more potential outbreaks.

item.title: Fallen rock climber to be rescued in NSW
item.description: A helicopter has been sent out to winch an injured man who fell while rock climbing in the Blue Mountains.
